  selfthebrand: {
    description:
      "In 2020, Nayra faced challenges in finding products that matched the aesthetic and requirements of her self-care routine. SELF emerged from a phone call and a few walks through Cairo, on a quest for a microfiber towel and a satin pillowcase.\n\nThey are committed to promoting equal working opportunities for women & having their customers feel that their voices are heard and their experiences are represented and connected through everything they create.\n\nTheir story is one about solidarity; it’s about unity, support, reliance, and comfort. As a brand founded by women with the help of other women, here at SELF, they believe in the importance of sticking together and helping each other out.\nThat’s when they felt that their skin-care routine needs some assistance and aiding, and with the support of women and men from across Egypt, they present to you SELF.\n\nBorn in Cairo, Egypt, SELF now operates from Alexandria. Their mission is to craft a multitude of products in Egypt using 100% Egyptian fabric.\n\nThe vision centers on ensuring premium quality, with their success deeply rooted in empowering women.",
    logo: "/logos/selfthebrand.avif",
  },
  najlah: {
    description:
      "For many years, clothing has caused a lot of anxiety for women, binding them to certain styles and fits, based on societal norms and expectations, body types and skin tones, slowly crippling them into thinking that they cannot wear a certain item if they do not look a certain way. Najlah is an authentic Egyptian brand that celebrates the inherent power of all women, presenting them with a variety of clothes in which women of all sizes can wring out and freely express themselves. \nMost of Najlah's products are free-sized since the brand wanted to use non-traditional sizing to promote inclusivity and comfort, rather than complicating feelings with body image. Najlah is here to remind all women that clothes are meant to fit them, not the other way around!",
    logo: "/logos/najlah.avif",
  },
  notfound: {
    description:
      "WHAT'S NOTFOUND ELSEWHERE.\n\nNOTFOUND is a unisex brand founded by two step-sisters: Dina Tarek and Tamara Sherif\nTheir passion for styling minimal streetwear inspired the creation of must-have essentials in their hometown Cairo.\nThe name ‘NOTFOUND’ stems from the struggle of finding high quality essentials at a fair price. Their aim is to create essentials that draw influences from comfort and minimalism that cater to the everyday individual.",
    logo: "/logos/notfound.png",
  },
  asili: {
    logo: "/logos/asili.svg",
    description:
      "Introducing Asili: a captivating blend of Egyptian heritage and contemporary style, crafted to celebrate the rich tapestry of Egypt's cultural legacy while embracing the spirit of modernity.\n\nAsili, meaning origin or essence in Swahili, stands as a testament to the roots from which it draws inspiration—the vibrant heritage of Egypt. Born from a deep appreciation for the country's ancient traditions, Asili reimagines these timeless elements through a contemporary lens, offering a fresh perspective on Egyptian fashion.\n\nEach garment from Asili is a work of art, meticulously designed to seamlessly blend traditional Egyptian motifs, colors, and craftsmanship with modern silhouettes and materials. From intricately embroidered patterns reminiscent of Pharaonic symbols to bold geometric prints inspired by the bustling streets of Cairo, every piece tells a story of heritage and innovation.\n\nAt the heart of Asili's ethos lies a commitment to sustainability and ethical practices. Drawing upon Egypt's rich textile heritage, Asili sources high-quality, locally sourced materials, ensuring minimal environmental impact and supporting local artisans and craftsmen.\n\nWhether it's a sleek modern dress adorned with traditional Egyptian embroidery or a chic ensemble infused with vibrant colors inspired by the Nile River, Asili offers a diverse range of clothing that effortlessly blends the past with the present, allowing wearers to embrace their heritage while stepping boldly into the future.\n\nDiscover Asili—where the essence of Egypt's rich cultural heritage meets the pulse of modern fashion, creating a unique and timeless style that resonates with the soul of the contemporary world.",
  },
  baynoire: {
    logo: "/logos/Baynoire.svg",
    description: "",
  },
  escala: {
    logo: "/logos/escala.svg",
    description:
      "We’re a team of passionate fashion enthusiasts who believe that clothing should be more than just a way to cover your body – it should be a form of self-expression, a statement of your personality, and a reflection of your values. \nOur journey started with a simple idea – to create a clothing brand that would offer the best possible quality at affordable prices, while also being environmentally conscious and socially responsible. We wanted to create clothes that would not only look good but also feel good, both on your skin and on your conscience. \nEST. 2023 \nWORLDWIDE DELIVERY \nThat’s why we’ve made it our mission to use only the best materials and production methods, to ensure that our clothes are not only stylish but also durable and sustainable. We work with some of the best designers and manufacturers in the industry, who share our vision of creating clothes that are both fashionable and ethical. \nAt Escala, we believe that fashion should be accessible to everyone. That’s why we offer a wide range of styles, from street wear to casual wear, and everything in between. Whether you’re looking for an eye-catching t-shirt, a stylish shirt, or a trendy accessory, we’ve got you covered. \nBut we’re not just about clothes – we’re also about community. We believe that fashion is a way to connect people from all walks of life, to celebrate diversity, and to inspire creativity. That’s why we encourage our customers to share their style and their stories with us, to be part of our #EscalaCommunity, and to help us create a more inclusive and sustainable fashion industry. \nSo, whether you’re a fashionista, a trendsetter, or just someone who wants to look good and feel good, we invite you to join us on this journey. Explore our collections, discover your style, and be part of a movement that’s changing the way we think about fashion. \nThank you for choosing Escala – where fashion meets conscience.",
  },
  juvenile: {
    logo: "/logos/juvenile.svg",
    description:
      "At Juvenile, we do create streetwear; we craft an artistic expression of life. We're more than a brand; we're a movement that celebrates the beauty in simplicity and the power of youthful energy. Our mission is to inspire individuals to embrace their creativity while embracing a modern, minimalistic lifestyle.\n\nMinimal Streetwear\n\nOur collections are a fusion of contemporary style and minimalism. We believe in the power of simplicity, the elegance of clean lines, and the beauty of understated aesthetics. Our streetwear is designed for those who appreciate the fine balance between self-expression and subtlety. We make a statement. \n\nWhat 'Verve' Means to Us\n\n'Verve' is the new State of Mind. It's that electrifying surge of energy that accompanies the moments of youthful exuberance. It's the passion that drives us to be a dynamic force in our community. We've made it our mission to embody 'Verve' in everything we do, from our designs to our community engagement.\n\nOur Commitment\n\nWe're not just here to provide you with streetwear; we're here to inspire you. Our commitment is to empower this generation to express themselves authentically and without inhibition. We're more than a clothing brand; we're a platform for creative souls to shine.\n\nWelcome to JUVENILE Fam. Make a statement, and make it minimal.",
  },
